    "In the following paper, they applied 1D-CNN to address the binary damage detection problem, distinguishing between undamaged and damaged cases 8.",
    "Based on simulated",
    "The crack detection problem of a solid structure can be formalized as follows: Given a solid structure represented by a physical domain ⊂ R n (n = 2, 3), an internal crack can be written as a function φ(x) = 1, where x ∈ R n is a point in the domain.",
    "The intact area is represented as φ(x) = 0.",
    "Given N sensors at fixed locations x 0, • • •, x i, • • •, x N, the recorded wave data at time t of sensor location x i is denoted as u (i,t)."
